The paper deals with a variant of the knapsack problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves dynamic programming, which is a common technique used in optimization problems and falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also proposes a new dynamic programming technique, which involves heavy-light recursive dynamic programming, and this technique falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of fully polynomial-time approximation schemes, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT).
